CorpGov is pleased to announce the agenda for the second Princeton CorpGov Forum to be held Thursday, May 21, 2026 at The Nassau Inn in Princeton, New Jersey. Our roster of speakers features industry leaders and alumni spanning five decades at Princeton, with topics encompassing university endowments, shareholder activism, private equity, venture capital, private and public capital markets, entertainment and the finance of college sports. The forum, hosted in The Prince William Ballroom, includes an afternoon of panels, firesides and networking, followed by a reception with cocktails and heavy hors d’oeuvres.
REGISTER HERE
Agenda – Thursday, May 21
2:00 pm – Registration and Networking – The Prince William Ballroom
3:00 pm – Forum Begins – The Prince William Ballroom
Endowments: Governance and Alternative Investments
Activism: Governance from Investor and Board Perspectives
AI and Cybersecurity in the Boardroom
Governance in Private Equity: From Investment to Exit
Public and Private Capital Markets Assessment
The Business of Entertainment and Advertising
Finance of Sports: Collegiate Focus
6:00 pm – Cocktail Reception – The Prince William Ballroom
The event will be digitized into a report published on CorpGov and content partners Yahoo Finance, Bloomberg Terminals, Reuters via LSEG Workspace, and AlphaSense, filmed in 4K with professional editing.
We invite all members of the Princeton community along with institutional investors and operating company executives. For more information, please email Editor@CorpGov.com.
